(24, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Front Desk Associate', 'front-desk-associate', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<p> Ensures the security of all guests privacy is maintained at all times.<br> Ensures the highest standards of total quality and customer service. The incumbent must possess a welcoming<br>manner, positive attitude and honesty, demonstrate effective communication skills; professionally interact with<br>residents/guests; answering resident/guest questions concerning housing/lodging facilities; and provide information<br>about local attractions. Work involves multiple/changing priorities and time sensitive/confidential information.<br> Receives requests and processes reservations within established guidelines. Utilizes the Property Management<br>System (PMS) to access/register guest information, retrieve/change/cancel/confirm reservations, and coordinate<br>group registration and check-out. Verifies registration information and secures guests mode of payment for<br>incidental expenses and room charges.<br> Registers and assigns rooms to residents/guests, issue room keycards, transmit/receive messages, keep records<br>of occupied rooms/guest accounts, and present statements to collect payments as necessary. Prepare registration<br>packets for the next day arrivals to include registration card, room keycards, floor plan map, and other information.<br> Incumbent is responsible for a variety of different and unrelated functions. Receives and is accountable for the<br>NGIS change fund. Prepares Close Bank Report and secures NGIS cash receipts at the end of each shift in<br>accordance with established procedures.<br> Responsible for the accountability of all the master/room keycards, and any other inventory maintained at front<br>desk. Back up file of keycard system.<br> May be required to run and print various reports from the PMS: Expected Arrivals, Departure List, In-House Guest<br>List and Night Audit reports. Assists in creating daily, monthly, and annual occupancy reports. Coordinate with<br>Operations Department to validate room status for occupancy and reconcile room status with the Housekeeper<br>reports to ensure rooms are ready for occupancy.<br> Sets up direct bills where appropriate and liaisons with Accounting for billing questions/issues. Verifies charges for<br>correctness, makes appropriate changes if error occurs, and completes all computer generated reports as assigned<br>and notates any delinquent accounts/discrepancies for action by management.<br> Provides assistance when handling customer complaints, resolving problems in a tactful manner. Situations<br>involving unfamiliar problems not covered by instructions are referred to the lead/assistant manager/manager for<br>resolution. Answers phones and transfers calls to appropriate individuals/departments. Logs trouble calls and<br>ensures the appropriate department is notified. Relocate resident/guest to a different room when required. Logs<br>pass down incidents to relieving shift for reference.<br> Logs and tracks in PMS Lost and Found items, contacts the resident/guest who lost the item, and retrieves the<br>same item for return.<br> Maintain logbook of locked out resident/guest, validate identity prior to issuance of 1-day lockout keycard. Provides<br>escorts in resident/guest rooms after normal duty hours or during emergency requiring security, safety, fire, medical,<br>and maintenance assistance.<br> Ensure extra supplies, amenities, cleaning equipment, and linen are available after normal duty hours for<br>resident/guest requirements.<br> The incumbent is required to execute policies, regulations, and guidelines as they pertain to a wide variety of<br>procedures and internal controls. Consult with assistant manager/manager when work practices, techniques,<br>records, and other functions are not in compliance with instructions.<br> Fully implements all safety, fire prevention, SDS and environmental/industrial hygiene requirements. Ensures<br>appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) as instructed is properly used.<br> Keeps the front desk and lobby area clean, neat, and orderly in appearance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must speak, read, and understand the English language.</li>\r\n<li>Must possess basic math, reading and computer skills.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>1. Must have at least completed 2-years college course or 2-years of work experience that demonstrates<br>knowledge of basic principle, concepts, standards, regulations and administration related to hospitality<br>operations, customer service, reservations, front desk, and night audit functions.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>1. Ability to handle, control, and account for large amount of cash.<br>2. Working knowledge of cleaning procedures and proper use of cleaning equipment and approved,<br>commonly used chemicals (including Safety Data Sheet), and adhere to basic safety, environmental, and<br>fire prevention policies, procedures, and regulations as required.<br>3. Must be proficient with calculator and basic computer software (word processing and spreadsheet),<br>including knowledge of the property management system. Property Management System (PMS) training<br>is provided.<br>4. CNIC Navy Lodging Program Front Desk Certification and Annual Re-certification are provided.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to vacancies@amsol.africa by 6th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '$ 540', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-22 10:32:22', '2025-05-22 10:33:42', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(25, 1, NULL, NULL, 'CASHIER', 'cashier', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Performs cashier responsibilities to man and operate the Marina Pro Shop Counter, monitors and records VHF<br>radio and telephone communication.</li>\r\n<li>The incumbent picks up cash change fund and delivers monetary sales bag and Daily Activity Report<br>(DAR) to the MWR Central Cashier before opening and after closing of the Marina Pro-Shop Counter.</li>\r\n<li>Performs selling of pro-shop merchandizes, provides equipment rental to customers, collect rental<br>fees, enters collected fees into the cash drawers and issues official receipts to customers.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains Marina rental reservations, monitors, schedules and coordinates LCM and Deep-sea<br>Fishing charters.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains and monitors Mako and ski boats reservations.</li>\r\n<li>Performs requisitioning of merchandize and maintains proper storage.</li>\r\n<li>The incumbent coordinates with chartering customer, Deep-sea Boat Captain and or Annex-06 for<br>scheduled fishing trip.</li>\r\n<li>Conducts and maintains accurate inventories and records of Marina merchandizes, prepares,<br>reviews, evaluates and submits Certificate of Dispositions (CODs) and NAFI purchase requisitions for<br>approval of authorized MWR Management personnel.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares and submits monthly inventory records and reports to NAF MWR Accounting Office at<br>specified timeframes via Marina Manager.</li>\r\n<li>Alternates Marina Storekeeper as required. Promptly reports Marina issues and concerns to Marina<br>Manager.</li>\r\n<li>Other duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must be familiar with requisitions, invoices, official receipts, or other procurement related documents<br>that may serve as support to receive/issue materials or equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Must be computer literate, capable to use calculators and cash drawers/registers. Familiar with<br>Microsoft Windows Excel applications</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Must be able to communicate effectively in English language, both verbally and in writing.</li>\r\n<li>Must speak, read, and understand the English language.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Must have a current driver&rsquo;s license, can drive a pick-up truck up to 3/4-ton capacity.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">CPR &amp; First Aid Training certification</span><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Star Service </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Customer Service Training</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Fleet and Family Readiness Cash Handling Training</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Must be a Diploma graduate.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&middot; Must have at least two (2) year of experience as cashier and customer service oriented. Marina<br>operations and maintenance support experience preferred.<br>Submitted</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to<em><strong> vacancies@amsol.afri</strong></em>ca by 6th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 510', 3, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-22 11:26:03', '2025-05-22 11:28:30', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(26, 1, NULL, NULL, 'HOUSEKEEPER', 'housekeeper', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensures the highest standards of total quality and customer service are maintained. Ensure guest privacy and<br>security is maintained at all times.</li>\r\n<li>Must possess a welcoming manner, positive attitude and honesty, demonstrate effective communication skills;<br>professionally interact with guests; answering guest questions concerning lodging facilities; and provide information<br>about local attractions. Provide assistance in handling guest complaints, involving management as necessary.</li>\r\n<li>Perform daily housekeeping duties as required, which includes, but not limited to: dusting/polishing furniture; trash<br>removal and replace wastebasket liners; vacuuming and/or sweeping floors; cleaning/sanitizing bathrooms and<br>kitchen areas (to include all sinks, showers, tubs, toilets, floors, microwaves, refrigerators, ovens, cooktops,<br>counters, cupboards): making beds and removing/changing beddings; restocking amenities, bed and bath linens,<br>and other guest room supplies, checking condition of room assets and reporting problems to Housekeeper<br>Lead/Operations Supervisor.; and responding to guest requests and communications.</li>\r\n<li>Count and sort linen from individual rooms along with clean linen issued to during assigned shift. Sort, fold, bundle<br>and issue/return linen in accordance with established instructions and/or is directed by Housekeeper<br>Lead/Operations Supervisor. Prepare linen in/out report daily to Warehouse, ensuring any missing/damaged linen<br>is reported. Process MR (Mess Requisition) to replenish supplies, amenities and linen to sustain par standards set<br>by management.</li>\r\n<li>Checked out rooms must complete all daily cleaning duties listed in Item 4 and ensure room is ready for occupancy<br>by a new guest.</li>\r\n<li>Perform deep cleaning as required in accordance with the Accreditation Standard.</li>\r\n<li>Perform custodial duties in all the lobbies, passageways, stairwells, public restroom, laundry room, storage room.<br>Maintain appearance of external areas of buildings, to include walkways, entryways, paths, sidewalks and driveway.<br>Ensure cleanliness of gazebos, patios, smoking shelters, bike racks and/or shelters, barbecue grills, outdoor<br>furniture, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Complete room status report providing status of all assigned common areas/rooms (vacant, check-out, occupied)<br>and turn in report to Housekeeper Lead/Operations Supervisor before lunch break and at the end of each work day.<br>Maintain documentation of work performed on a daily basis.</li>\r\n<li>Promptly inform Lead/Supervisor of missing, malfunctioning or damaged items in rooms and/or common areas.<br>Process request for replacement of defective, unserviceable, and/or damaged appliances and equipment. Notify<br>Lead/Supervisor of any valuables (i.e. cash, jewelry, electronic gadgets, etc) left out in the open by guests before<br>cleaning the room or common area. Immediately report to Lead/Supervisor breaches of discipline found in assigned<br>building upon detection.</li>\r\n<li>Relocate heavy, bulky items such as furniture, supplies, and linen (clean and dirty) by hand or using carts or dollies.</li>\r\n<li>Assist management with the facility&rsquo;s inventory control program by: conducting annual inventory of assets located<br>in room, lounges, common areas, and outdoor furniture, appliances, and equipment (FA&amp;E); ensure assets are<br>tagged; track asset movements in and out of the building from replacement cycle, improvements, repairs, or<br>damages.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in all announced and unannounced inspections of assigned building. Act as an escort with Public Works<br>or other contractors require access to rooms and common areas. Monitor work of custodial, maintenance and other<br>workers in assigned building, and report discrepancies to the Lead/Supervisor.</li>\r\n<li>Perform operational and minor maintenance actions including but not limited to: change the battery of alar/wall<br>clocks and TV/DVD remote controls; change light bulbs of desk, end tables, nightstand, and floor lamps; and<br>monthly inspection of fire extinguishers. Initiate maintenance service (routine or emergency) calls by reporting&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must possess basic math, reading and computer skills.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>1. Must have at least completed a diploma as a housekeeper and (1) work experience or similar in the lodging<br>industry.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>1. Ability to apply general knowledge of cleaning procedures and proper use of cleaning equipment and<br>approved commonly used chemicals (including Safety Data Sheet), and adhere to basic safety,<br>environmental, and fire prevention policies, procedures, and regulations as required.<br>2. Must be proficient with calculator and basic computer software (word processing and spreadsheet)..<br>3. CNIC Navy Lodging Program Housekeeper Certification and Annual Re-certification are provided.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 510', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-22 11:46:52', '2025-05-22 11:47:23', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(27, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Warehouseman', 'warehouseman', '<p><strong>OVERVIEW:</strong><br>&bull; Responsible for off-loading subsistence and supply items, removing delivered items from pallets, and<br>storing items per PWS requirements.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&bull; Performing inventories, audits, verifying materials (or merchandise) against receiving documents, noting<br>and reporting discrepancies and obvious damages.<br>&bull; Routing materials to prescribed storage locations.<br>&bull; Storing, stacking, or palletizing materials IAW prescribed storage methods, rearranging and taking<br>inventory of stored materials, examining stored materials and reporting deterioration and damage, and<br>removing material from storage.<br>&bull; Issue and receive parts, supplies, and material to customers out of a variety of stores and maintain records<br>of all transactions.<br>&bull; Operate hand or power trucks in performing warehousing duties.<br>&bull; Performs mandatory periodic audit\\inventory actions, interacts with customers; updates computer systems,<br>and maintains 100% accountability of all transactions and warehouse inventories.<br>&bull; Performs other duties as assigned to meet organizational/operational objectives.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>(Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs):</p>\r\n<p><br>&bull; Knowledgeable in warehouse operations, issues, sorts, receives, processes, and stores material and<br>stocks.<br>&bull; Knowledge of supplies, equipment, and/or services ordering and inventory control.<br>&bull; Must possess administrative, organizational, and computer skills to include proficiency with Microsoft Office<br>suite.<br>&bull; Proven ability to organize, prioritize, and follow through to completion on multiple tasks, under strict<br>deadlines and changing priorities.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must have a valid and be able to obtain driver&rsquo;s license with the following codes (2,3 or B1, B2 or D).<br>&bull; Must be able to operate material handling equipment such as forklift, pallet jack, man lift etc.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Safety Data Sheets (SDS) and storage requirements to meet compatibility of products based<br>on hazard class is required.</li>\r\n<li>Must speak, read, and understand the English language.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Completed Logistics course from TESDA is a plus:<br>➢ Warehousing Services - NC II, III, IV</p>\r\n<p><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Minimum of three (3) years of military experience in warehousing and supply operations desired or<br>comparable civilian experience.<br>&bull; Experience in maintenance and supply documentation and procedures.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 540', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-22 12:31:31', '2025-05-22 12:32:34', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(28, 1, NULL, NULL, 'VEHICLE MECHANIC', 'vehicle-mechanic', '<p><strong>OVERVIEW:</strong><br>Responsible for safely and efficiently performing maintenance, repairs, and services to light vehicle<br>equipment.<br><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Receives task assignments from Foreman to which assigned.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Accomplishes assigned task even without Foreman&rsquo;s presence.</li>\r\n<li>Diagnoses and performs all repairs to vehicles specifically the buses used in the shuttle runs.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Perform preventive maintenance (PM) to all vehicles turned in to Shop on a quarterly basis.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Troubleshoots automotive electrical systems using meters and technical manuals, electrical schematics.<br>Rewires electrical components, wiring harnesses, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Removes, repairs, and replaces assemblies such as alternators, generators, starters &amp; other electrical<br>systems and put vehicles into operational status.</li>\r\n<li>Operates and maintains recovery vehicles and associated accessories and equipment.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Performs recovery and evacuation operations for abandoned, damaged, or disabled light or heavy wheel or<br>track vehicles.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Determines the method of recovery and associated equipment to be employed.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Makes minor repairs and adjustments to disabled vehicles.</li>\r\n<li>Maneuvers recovery vehicles, selecting most desirable positions for wreckers, trailers, full-tracked recovery<br>vehicles, or transporters, and attaches hoists, cables, chains, or slings to vehicles to facilitate drawing for<br>lifting disabled vehicles.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Raises, moves pulls and secures vehicles, components, or equipment using accessories such as winches,<br>cranes, booms, jacks, blocks, and tackles, and by applying necessary lines and rigs.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Instructs and assists lower skilled personnel in all phases of wheel and track vehicle recovery and evacuation<br>and use of all associated accessories and equipment.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Plans, organizes, and supervises recovery operations and assigns duties to recovery personnel.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Performs other related duties that may be assigned by Foreman and Superintendent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;(Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Must know machines and tools, including their designs, uses, repair, and maintenance.</li>\r\n<li>Familiar with the usage of computer-based technical manuals preferred.</li>\r\n<li>Must have the ability to troubleshoot, determine the causes of operating errors, and decide what to do about<br>them.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must have at least a diploma, Mechanical engineering or vocational course graduate is required.<br>EXPERIENCE:<br>&bull; Minimum of two (2) years&rsquo; journeyman level experience in vehicle and equipment maintenance and repair<br>either on BSVE, WHE, MHE, and Ordinance Handling Equipment.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 570', 4, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-22 13:34:58', '2025-05-22 13:35:36', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(29, 1, NULL, NULL, 'ABS WELDER', 'abs-welder', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Performs shipboard welding services/processes for the repair and maintenance of piping system,<br>machinery, structural system and other related work on Military Sealift Command vessels and<br>prepositioned ships in DGAR that are either leased to the US Government or owned by the United<br>States Government.<br>a) Joins metal parts by the use of electric arc, oxy-acetylene or other gaseous welding or brazing<br>equipment &amp; machinery according to blueprints and welding process specifications.<br>b) Performs cutting and burning, pre-heats or anneal metals using flame torches.<br>c) Welds in all position various types of metals and alloys including, but not limited to high-tensile steel,<br>CU-NI alloys and aluminum, in various shapes and sizes using manual, semi-automatic arc or gas<br>welding methods (MIG or TIG) or combination of both.<br>d) Identifies metal characteristics, ascertain applicable electrode or fillers and appropriate welding<br>process for each job.<br>e) Cuts, bevel and gauges ferrous and non-ferrous metals using manual, semi-automatic arc and gas<br>flame equipment.<br>f) Lays-out, fabricate and fit pipes or metal plates during repair or fabrication, using blueprints and<br>applicable drawings as work guide.<br>&bull; Responsible for the safe operation of equipment, maintains awareness to job safety requirements at all<br>times and keeps all work areas clean &amp; in good housekeeping. Works in the environment of shipboard<br>hazards and operating machineries.<br>&bull; Part of Riding Gang onboard ships while deployed away from DGAR on an as needed basis to continue<br>maintenance requirements began while anchored in the lagoon.<br>&bull; Performs other duties as assigned.<br>&bull; Personnel is required to work for an additional two (2) hours every regular working days as an expected<br>requirement delineated under Spec Item 3.4.2 of A-06 Contract.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>(Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs)<br>&bull; ABS Certified, minimum of 6G-P1 (high-pressure vessel / pipe welding) qualification.<br>&bull; Must have knowledge in metallurgy and familiar with various alloy welding processes, with at least<br>minimum working knowledge on high-tensile steel, CU-NI and Aluminum.<br>&bull; Must have the ability to read and interpret blueprints, mechanical drawings and sketches.<br>&bull; Must speak, read and understand English language both orally and in writing.<br>&bull; Must pass the overseas medical screening and be in good health.</p>\r\n<p><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ABS 6G-P1 (high-pressure vessel / pipe welding) with visual and non-destructive test certification (RT)</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Welding Technology Course not lower than 6G-SMAW.</li>\r\n<li>Trade school training or apprenticeship course in Welding Technology, complete with Shop<br>Mathematics, Metalworking / Metallurgy and Mechanical Drawing.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br>EDUCATION:<br>&bull;Diploma graduate / vocational or apprenticeship course related to Welding Technology.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Minimum of five (5) year experience as Journeyman Welder or Marine Welder in Naval Ship Repair Facility,<br>commercial shipyard or oil refineries; with working knowledge and experience in alloys and high-pressure<br>vessel/piping welding operations complete with radiographic test (x-ray quality) requirements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 1,392', 1, 'part-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-23 08:31:47', '2025-05-23 09:19:44', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(30, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Water System Operator', 'water-system-operator', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br>&bull; Performs daily tasks and work orders involving water treatment and distribution operations, maintenance, and installation.<br>&bull; Operates treatment systems to ensure demands for FFHC and non-FFHC water and quality criteria are met continuously.<br>&bull; Distributes FFHC and non-FFHC water to ensure demands and quality criteria are met continuously.<br>&bull; Collects and records periodic systems readings such as flow rates, system pressure, analyzer/sensor &amp; meter readings, etc.<br>&bull; Adjusts Water Plant equipment, ensuring operational guidelines are followed and are in compliance with all federal, state, and U.S. Navy guidelines.<br>&bull; Operates, monitors, maintains, and repairs Nano Reverse Osmosis water treatment/distribution systems, including but not limited to wells, pumps, water catchments and storage systems, water filtration treatment plants, distribution piping, valves, flow control devices, taps, line stops, backflows, chlorination/dechlorination, leak detection, and analyzers.<br>&bull; Conduct daily operations and maintenance inspections of assigned areas such as checking chemical feed systems, water collection, and storage sites, water filtration treatment plants, and facility distribution system components.<br>&bull; Operates equipment to purify and clarify water including reject water.<br>&bull; Cleans and maintains equipment, tanks, pressure filters, and other work areas.<br>&bull; Responds to Water Plant emergencies with appropriate immediate and subsequent actions.<br>&bull; Performs maintenance program for water systems to ensure all equipment and components are effectively maintained, remain in optimum condition, and sustain maximum life.<br>&bull; Performs preventive maintenance program for the raw water supply, WTP, and distribution system equipment to ensure proper operation, minimize breakdowns, and maximize useful life. &bull; Observe and follow all safety rules and procedures, including wearing required personal protective equipment.<br>&bull; Performs other work-related duties and responsibilities as assigned to meet organizational/operational objectives.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must possess administrative, organizational, and computer skills to include proficiency with Microsoft Office suite including (MS Word, PowerPoint, Excel, and Outlook).</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to organize, prioritize, and follow through to completion of multiple tasks, under strict deadlines, and changing priorities.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work quickly and in a potentially high-stress environment.</li>\r\n<li>Comfort with multi-tasking and handling multiple requests from different individuals and departments.</li>\r\n<li>Must speak, read, and understand the English Language.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li>Must have a valid driver&rsquo;s license with the following license codes (B, B1, B2, C, D, BE, and CE) and be able to operate the assigned vehicles.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Satisfactorily completed the training course and exam provided by the Navy Operator Certification Authority (NOCA) Board.<br>o Level 1 Overseas Drinking Water Treatment System Operator<br>o Level 1 Overseas Drinking Water Distribution System Operator</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must be at least a Diploma, Vocational, or Technical course graduate related to electrical or mechanical required.<br>EXPERIENCE:<br>&bull; Must have at least one (1) year of experience working in water treatment and distribution facilities.<br>&bull; Must have experience in pumps and chemical feeders repair.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 754', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-23 08:44:44', '2025-05-23 09:25:47', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(31, 1, NULL, NULL, 'LABORER', 'laborer', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&middot; Assists the Boat Captain in the movement and requirements of the vessel during operations.<br>&middot; Handles boat&rsquo;s mooring line, fenders, and or towing line during towing, docking and undocking of<br>vessel.<br>&middot; Assists Boat Captain in performing boat pre-operational check prior to underway operation and boat<br>securing.<br>&middot; Checks navigation lights, first aid medical kit, firefighting and lifesaving equipment.<br>&middot; Maintains and secures mooring and anchor lines, fire extinguishers and boat cleanliness.<br>&middot; The incumbent performs scheduled maintenance and adheres to all industrial and afloat safety<br>procedures, directives and boating safety requirements at all times.<br>&middot; Provides briefing to patrons concerning boating safety and local regulations before getting underway<br>as required by the Boat Captain.<br>&middot; Reports discrepancies and safety hazard immediately to the Boat Captain. Provides assistance to the<br>customers in rigging lures into the fishing reel lines.<br>&middot; Provides look-out to the Boat Captain during poor visibility and or as required by the Boat Captain.<br>&middot; Assists patrons during fishing activity, i.e., fish gaffing, and whacking of caught fish prior to unhooking<br>of lures for safety.<br>&middot; Stores fish aboard the vessel.<br>&middot; Advises patrons&rsquo; position while fishing to prevent lines caught by propellers.<br>&middot; Performs offloading of customer&rsquo;s fish.<br>&middot; Performs checking of engine cooling systems while underway, performs boat cleaning, fueling and oil<br>top-up prior and after the boat operations.<br>&middot; Perform other duties/tasks as required.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must speak and write English language fluently and able to swim.</li>\r\n<li>Must be trained in customer service, mission oriented and has the ability to deal with multi-national<br>customer.</li>\r\n<li>No physical handicap limiting functions aboard vessels and proficiency in small boat handling is<br>required.</li>\r\n<li>Must possess valid Driver&rsquo;s License.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&middot; CPR/AED and First Aid Training.<br>&middot; Star Customer Service Training.<br>&middot; Be able to pass Final Basic Boat Crewmember (301) and Personnel Qualification Standards (PQS) test<br>by Harbor Pilot.</strong></p>\r\n<p><br><strong>EDUCATION</strong>:<strong><br>&middot; Must be a diploma graduate, Nautical School graduate preferred.<br>EXPERIENCE:<br>&middot; One (1) year experience aboard vessel as deckhand.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 570', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-23 09:03:24', '2025-05-23 09:21:30', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(32, 1, NULL, NULL, 'MARINE MECHANIC', 'marine-mechanic', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>Responsible for the preventive maintenance, pre operational check and testing of all MWR motorized boats.<br>&middot; The incumbent performs diagnosing of problems, repairs and operational test of all types of Marina<br>recreational craft with Digital Throttle and shift System (DTS) Verado mercury outboard engines.<br>&middot; Performs minor and major repairs, overhaul, removal, replacement, installation, alignment,<br>operational tests, adjustments of components, accessories, propulsion sand auxiliary systems of<br>powered boats to include but not limited to both outboard and inboard gasoline and diesel engines.<br>&middot; Accomplishes repairs, removal, installation and testing of low voltage electrical system of the<br>watercraft. Uses shop tools and equipment such as digital engine analyzer, battery tester, computer<br>diagnostic system (CDS), battery charger, multi-testers, grinders, drills, gauges, micrometers, calipers<br>and other related shop maintenance equipment. Installs and removes small outboard engines on<br>sailboats as per customer&rsquo;s request and provides safety line on outboards.<br>&middot; Certifies sea worthiness of powered boats prior to get underway.<br>&middot; Initiates material request for outboard/inboard engines and boats to maintain acceptable level of<br>material support.<br>&middot; Performs watercraft and Marina facility cleaning and securing after completion of boat maintenance/<br>repair works.<br>&middot; Secures hazardous materials after each usage for safety of all MWR personnel and patrons.<br>&middot; The incumbent adheres to all industrial and afloat safety procedures and requirements at all time.<br>&middot; Provide briefing to Marina patrons concerning boating safety and local regulations ad required.<br>&middot; Reports discrepancies and safety hazards immediately to Marina supervisor or Manager.<br>&middot; Performs other duties /tasks as required.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS</strong><br>&middot; Must have knowledge in the marina engineering field, gasoline/diesel engine propulsion systems and<br>outboard / inboard engines.<br>&middot; Must be able to read and interpret technical drawings, operation and maintenance manuals.<br>&middot; Must possess valid driver&rsquo;s License.</p>\r\n<p><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Outboard/Inboard Engine Training, Diesel Engine Training</li>\r\n<li>Powered Boat Operations</li>\r\n<li>Adult First Aid, CPR/AED certification</li>\r\n<li>Star Customer service Training</li>\r\n<li>Must speak, read, and understand the English language.</li>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&middot; Must be A diploma graduate, coupled with completion of an apprenticeship of trade school training<br>in gasoline and diesel engine repairs.<br>EXPERIENCE:<br>&middot; Must have ten (10) years&rsquo; experience as a marine outboard/ inboard engine mechanic.<br>Submitted</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 624', 3, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-23 09:14:15', '2025-05-23 09:14:41', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1);
