(33, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Facility Planning Engineer', 'facility-planning-engineer', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br>&bull; Prepare and develop project documentation for all applicable projects as indicated by the Facilities<br>Readiness Evaluation System (FRES) to correct facility deficiencies, improve overall facility conditions, and<br>meet new mission requirements.<br>&bull; Develop Special Project documentation for projects subject to Special Project thresholds that are compliant<br>with OPNAVINST 11010.20 and NAVFACINST 11010.45.<br>&bull; Develop DD 1391 Project packages for projects subject to MCON funding thresholds IAW OPNAVINST<br>11010.20 and NAVFACINST 11010.45.<br>&bull; Revise and manage Basic Facility Requirements (BFRs) to ensure that they are current and correct.<br>&bull; Identify, develop, and prioritize facility projects for demolition, consolidation, reutilization, and joint use that<br>will result in maintenance and repair cost savings for the Navy.<br>&bull; Prepare, update, and maintain all real property records and conduct asset evaluations for Class 1 (land) and<br>Class 2 (facilities) Navy real property to accurately reflect existing conditions IAW NAVFAC P-78.<br>&bull; Prepare project site approval documentation to ensure facility projects are properly sited in compliance with<br>Regional Shore Infrastructure Planning (RSIPs) and land use regulations in a timely manner.<br>&bull; Provide facilities and technical services.<br>&bull; Prepares all Naval Shore Facilities planning documents including site approvals, special projects,<br>submission, MILCON submissions, and environmental impact reports as required.<br>&bull; Perform research and fieldwork.<br>&bull; Coordinates projects between the Navy, contractors, customers, and other parties as required.<br>&bull; Responsible for the overall evaluation and control of the assigned project schedules and performs schedule<br>development, maintenance, and monitoring of the planning/scheduling activities with minimal or no<br>supervisory oversight.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Demonstrates ability to develop engineering standards, specifications, guidelines, policies, and procedures.<br>&bull; Ability to work in a fast-paced environment that requires handling multiple tasks at a given time and rapidly<br>adapting to changing priorities and schedules.<br>&bull; Ability to read and interpret blueprints, diagrams, schematics, and written reference material, and follow<br>engineering drawings, specifications, and instructions.<br>&bull; Particular attention to detail, and good project management skills.<br>&bull; Must possess administrative, organizational, and computer skills to include proficiency with Microsoft Office<br>suite including (MS Word, PowerPoint, Excel, and Outlook).<br>&bull; Proficient in computer-assisted design (CAD) and other design, data recording, and analysis software.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must have a valid country of origin&rsquo;s driver\'s license and be able to operate the assigned vehicle.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Training in Shore Facilities Planning System and Special Projects Seminar.<br>&bull; American Institute of Certified Planners (AICP) certification is highly desired but not required.</p>\r\n<p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must have a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering (Civil, Electrical, Mechanical) or architecture, based on a four-year course of study from an accredited university or college.</p>\r\n<p><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Must have at least three (3) years of experience in planning and training in Shore Facilities Planning System<br>and Special Projects Seminar</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 1,600', 2, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-25 09:32:38', '2025-05-25 09:33:19', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(34, 1, NULL, NULL, 'HR Travel & Admin Coordinator', 'hr-travel-admin-coordinator', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\r\n<p><br><strong>Primary - Travel:</strong><br>&bull; The Travel Coordinator will arrange (business, emergency, and R&amp;R) travel for employees, identifying<br>the most cost-effective and efficient travel arrangements and making necessary reservations, including<br>flights, accommodation, transportation, and other necessary arrangements.<br>&bull; Research and compares available travel and hotel accommodation to identify the best available<br>option for each travel need.<br>&bull; When travel arrangements are within approved travel reasons and budget limits, make all<br>arrangements and reservations as requested.<br>&bull; Prepares travel itineraries and distributes travel arrangements and schedules to all appropriate staff.<br>&bull; Obtains approval from leadership for travel requests and expenses that exceed established limits.<br>&bull; Advises travelers and assists with any need for specialized travel documents such as visas,<br>passports, travel orders, APACS, and any necessary documentation needed for their travel.<br>&bull; Prepare and distribute travel itineraries, including all relevant details such as flight information, hotel<br>reservations, car rentals, and meeting schedules.<br>&bull; Ensure all travel arrangements are accurate, complete, and aligned with the traveler\'s and<br>company\'s preferences and requirements.<br>&bull; Manage and track travel expenses, including reconciling invoices, receipts, and credit card<br>statements to ensure compliance with company policies and budgetary constraints.<br>&bull; Assist employees in resolving any travel-related issues or emergencies, including flight<br>cancellations, missing connections, lost luggage, etc.<br>&bull; Maintain and update a database of employee travel profiles, including preferences, passport details,<br>and other relevant information.<br>&bull; Monitors and facilitates the use of company air travel credit cards.<br>&bull; Processes reimbursements for travel expenses.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Secondary - Admin:</strong><br>&bull; Conducts clerical duties including filing, answering phone calls, responding to emails, and preparing<br>and maintaining operations documents and reports.<br>&bull; Prepare requisition/MPR for all various office materials, supplies, and equipment and ensure it<br>adequate level of availability.<br>&bull; Monitors/maintains an accurate, and up-to-date inventory control system. Monitors/check daily<br>operations. Control and verify all data input into the system. Maintains a perpetual inventory system<br>ensuring the inventory is completely counted monthly and quarterly. Generally, monitors stock<br>control activities and provides technical assistance.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Liaise between departments for Lost &amp; Found and Compassionate that includes drafting emails or<br>letters on behalf of personnel involved.<br>&bull; Orchestrate special events and schedule and arrange meetings, make reservations and prepare<br>itineraries for new hire orientations and training.<br>&bull; Performs other work-related duti</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs):</strong></p>\r\n<p><br>&bull; Familiarity with budgeting and expense management processes.<br>&bull; Excellent organizational and time management skills.<br>&bull; Flexibility to adapt to changing travel arrangements and schedules.<br>&bull; Excellent attention to detail, ensuring accuracy in all travel arrangements and documentation.<br>&bull; Knowledge of travel policies, visa regulations, and international travel requirements.<br>&bull; Ability to handle and resolve travel-related issues or emergencies promptly and efficiently.<br>&bull; Proficient in using travel management software and tools to manage and track travel expenses.<br>&bull; Must possess administrative, organizational, and computer skills to include proficiency with<br>Microsoft Office suite including (MS Word, PowerPoint, Excel, and Outlook).<br>&bull; Proven ability to organize, prioritize, and follow through to completion of multiple tasks, under strict<br>deadlines and changing priorities.<br>&bull; Ability to convey information professionally and tactfully to individuals regarding sensitive and<br>confidential information and issues.<br>&bull; Ability to work quickly and in a potentially high-stress environment.<br>&bull; Comfort with multi-tasking and handling multiple requests from different individuals and<br>departments.<br>&bull; Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills to effectively interact with employees, vendors,<br>and travel agencies.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must possess country of origin&rsquo;s driver&rsquo;s license and be able to drive a manual and automatic<br>transmission vehicle.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; A Diploma is required; an associate\'s or bachelor&rsquo;s degree is preferred.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Previous work experience as a Travel Coordinator or a similar role in travel management, and in any<br>other administrative field capacity.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 1,260', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 11:53:41', '2025-05-26 14:06:55', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(35, 1, NULL, NULL, 'LABORATORY TECHNICIAN', 'laboratory-technician', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&middot; Performs sampling and quality surveillance of DLA capitalized products stored within DFSP DG.<br>&middot; Maintains updated and accurate record of test results, both on paper and in the FMDE program.<br>&middot; Carry out sampling and testing of petroleum products accurately and timely IAW the ASTM methods, MILSTD-3004, NAVAIR 00-80T-109, T.O. 42B-1-1, and other military standards.<br>&middot; Performs sampling on ships and verify conformity to specifications of product receipts.<br>&middot; Performs calibration, basic quality checks and minor troubleshooting of various laboratory equipment.<br>&middot; Operates laboratory equipment and instruments such as microscopes, centrifuge, agitators, viscosimeter,<br>chemical balance scales, spectrophotometer, gas chromatograph, colorimeter, and other equipment.<br>&middot; Prepares reports and other documents as required.<br>&middot; Prepares chemical solutions according to standard formulas.<br>&middot; Performs coordination roles for environmental and safety.<br>&middot; Upkeep cleanliness of work areas, apparatus and equipment<br>&middot; Maintain and manage storage of samples and other hazmats.<br>&middot; Performs other job, as directed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs):</strong><br>&middot; Requires general chemistry lab skills including basic laboratory safety and best practices.<br>&middot; Good mathematical and mechanical aptitude.<br>&middot; Must have good oral and written communication skills which enable effective liaison with clients, other<br>departments within the organization, subcontractors, and clients; reports directly to the Senior Fuel Chemist<br>&middot; Particular attention to detail, good project management skills.<br>&middot; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&middot; Must be contract-oriented and computer literate in Microsoft Office software.<br>&middot; Must be able to work with minimal supervision.<br>&middot; Can lift up to at least 15lbs.<br>&middot; Can climb fuel tanks of at least 30ft.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATION OR TRAINING</strong><br>&middot; Registered Chemist, Chemical Technologist or Chemical Engineer is highly desired but not required.<br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&middot; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Chemistry, Chemical Technology, Chemical Engineering, or other related field from an<br>accredited university or college.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&middot; Must have at least two (2) years of experience working in fuel laboratory or an analytical laboratory</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 1,020', 2, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 12:01:41', '2025-05-26 14:06:22', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(36, 1, NULL, NULL, 'LOCKSMITH', 'locksmith', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Repairs and opens locks, makes keys, and changes lock combinations, using hand tools and special equipment.<br>&bull; Disassembles locks, such as: padlocks, safe locks, door locks, and repairs or replaces worn tumblers, springs, and<br>other parts.<br>&bull; Moves lockpick in cylinder to open door locks without keys.<br>&bull; May keep records of company locks and keys.<br>&bull; Installs, adjusts and services locks and related equipment.<br>&bull; Prepares labour and material estimates.<br>&bull; Shortens tumblers and inserts new or repaired tumblers into lock to change combination.<br>&bull; Cuts new or duplicate keys using key machine, patterns, or codes.<br>&bull; Ensures proper care in the use and maintenance of equipment and supplies; promotes continuous improvement<br>of workplace safety and environmental practices.<br>&bull; Observes and follows all safety rules and procedures, including wearing required personal safety equipment.<br>&bull; Performs other duties and activities as directed.<br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS:</strong><br>&bull; Must have knowledge of the techniques for keying, repairing, installing and servicing locks and related hardware.<br>&bull; Must speak, read, and understand the English Language.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must have a valid Professional Driver&rsquo;s License with at least Restriction Code 2.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\"><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING:</strong><br>&bull; Must be qualified at the journeyman level and be a registered locksmith capable of providing total locksmith services<br>including high security locks.<br>&bull; Must have the ability to gain GSA and KABA X10 certification<br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must have at least a High School diploma, Vocational or Technical course graduate<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Must have at least three (3) years&rsquo; experience in locksmithing work.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '$ 650', 2, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 12:21:48', '2025-05-26 14:05:46', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(37, 1, NULL, NULL, 'LCM ENGINEER', 'lcm-engineer', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Works onboard craft and responsible for the safe operation and maintenance of Mechanized Landing Craft<br>(LCM) propulsion engine, machineries and auxiliary equipment. Work includes but are not limited to:<br>&bull; Pre-operational check, during operation and after operation checks of Diesel Engines;<br>propulsion/steering/ramp systems; hydraulic and fuel systems, and all other auxiliary equipment of each<br>boat run.<br>&bull; Performance of assigned scheduled (PMS) maintenance requirements on boat and onboard craft<br>equipment.<br>&bull; Troubleshooting, repair and diagnosing engines and equipment operation. Records and submits<br>equipment readings, makes adjustments and settings. Monitors and maintains within capabilities all<br>machinery in operational condition while underway.<br>&bull; The incumbent is part of the LCM crew that performs the following, in conjunction with various craft<br>operations:<br>a) Deployment, repositioning, installation of HP fender backing boards, towing of HP fenders, submarine<br>camels, sea cushion fenders and maintenance of NAVAID and fleet mooring buoys.<br>b) Retrieval/Deployment of submarine towed array sonar system (STASS) cable.<br>c) Assistance to Navy Underwater Construction Team (NUCT) or other diver inspection teams<br>performing U/W inspection of buoys, piers and markers; and to divers conducting hull cleaning,<br>inspection and U/W jobs for COMPSRON TWO ships.<br>d) MWR activities and chartered fishing trips, lagoon water sampling and special runs for VIP<br>repatriations or MEDEVACs.<br>e) Installation/positioning/retrieval of oil booms for ships, fuel barges and small craft operations.<br>f) Operation of YOS Potable water barge, SWOB, YC-SLOPS and YC-CARGO barge.<br>g) Search and Rescue operation and waterborne oil spill response, mitigation and clean-up.<br>h) Emergency requirements and other boat service assistance required in the lagoon.<br>i) Fuelling of craft in Small Boat Basin (SBB), removal of bilge oily water and cleaning of boat.<br>j) Dock and sea trials of LCMs, small boats and service crafts after repair/maintenance.<br>k) Mooring and unmooring of ships to/from Fleet Mooring Buoys and support to line handling of ships.<br>&bull; Participates in monthly oil spill drill and quarterly oil spill training, and NSF-DG Annual Facility Response<br>Training, accordingly.<br>&bull; Maintains awareness to safety requirements and all work areas clean, engine room, lazarette, and in good<br>housekeeping.<br>&bull; Perform duties as look-out to assist LCM Captain in the safe operation of LCM/Utility Boats, Rapid<br>Response Skimmer (RRS) and other tasks required to support contract requirements of A-06.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Knowledge in maintenance/troubleshooting and operation of boat propulsion diesel engines and<br>various machineries and mechanized equipment.<br>&bull; Familiar with shipboard mechanical system.<br>&bull; Must speak, read, and understand English language, both orally and in writing.<br>&bull; Must pass 2nd Class Swimmer qualification level<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Certified PQS 301 (Maintenance Personnel), Personnel Qualification Standard for Ship Maintenance<br>and Material Management (3M) System.<br>&bull; Satiscoxsw&bull; First Aid/CPR and 2nd Class Swimmer qualification certificate. &bull; Qual&bull; NSF-DG Facility Response Training.</p>\r\n<p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Diploma graduate and vocational course related to gasoline or diesel engine repair/mechanic.<br>&bull; Degree in engineering or formal schooling/apprenticeship course in inside machinist/mechanic is preferred<br>but not necessary.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>&bull; Minimum of three (3) year experience as Marine Mechanic or Boat Mechanic in Naval Ship Repair Facility or<br>commercial shipyard.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 553', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 12:37:52', '2025-05-26 14:05:11', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(38, 1, NULL, NULL, 'MARINE INBOARD MECHANIC', 'marine-inboard-mechanic', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; The incumbent must coordinate with his supervisor, all departmental matters requiring interface with<br>outside agencies.<br>&bull; Performs removal, repairs, overhauls, installations, mounting, alignment, trouble shooting and testing<br>of equipment, deck machineries, stationary diesel engines, cargo pumps, piping, marine diesel<br>propulsion engines, couplings, clutches, drive gears, reduction gears, propeller shafts, propellers<br>assemblies, cutlass bearings, staffing boxes, bilge pumps, air compressors, sea service power<br>generators sets, winches, wire rope, pumps, steering system, rudder system, hydraulic systems,<br>exhaust system, cooling systems and keel coolers.<br>&bull; Performs trouble shooting on any types of diesel engines, equipment under repairs, installation and<br>testing to make the shipboard equipment operational on the vessels or craft and industrial plant<br>equipment under the cognizant to A-06 Port Operations and all related systems and mechanical<br>work/activities, including but not limited to:<br>&bull; Removal, cleaning, preparation and installation and replacement of cutlass bearings, bushings, pins,<br>piping, machinery foundations, stuffing boxes, propeller shaft sealing systems and other related parts<br>prior of the craft/vessel under overhaul. Performs masking, covering and blanking of critical equipment<br>and surfaces for protection from any damaging elements.<br>&bull; Performs engine set up on dynamometer stand. Records reading, make adjustments and settings.<br>Installs temporary test equipment such as thermocouples, tachometers, pressure gauges and dial<br>indicators.<br>&bull; Performs repairs of blowers, compressors, and fuel injectors.<br>&bull; Maintains awareness to safety requirements, all work areas clean and in good housekeeping.<br>Accomplishes proper maintenance of various tools and equipment.<br>&bull; Performs other duties as required to support contract requirements.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Familiar with any type of marine diesel and gasoline engines, including marine outboard engines.<br>&bull; Knowledge in different types/classes and uses of tools and computerized diagnostic systems.<br>&bull; Must speak, read, and understand English language, both orally and in writing.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; High School graduate coupled with the completion of an apprenticeship or trade school training in diesel and<br>gasoline engine repairs.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE</strong>:<br>&bull; Minimum of four (4) year experience as an Equipment Mechanic, two (2) years of which must have been in<br>marine diesel engine repair work.<br>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING<br>&bull; Any mechanical specialized certification preferred, but not necessary.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 624', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 13:11:54', '2025-05-26 14:04:38', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(39, 1, NULL, NULL, 'DECKHAND LCM', 'deckhand-lcm', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Handles and secures mooring and towing lines during berthing/unberthing of craft and part of LCM<br>crew that performs the following, in conjunction with various craft operations:<br>a) Loading and off-loading of cargoes/supplies/dumpsters for delivery, from/to ships in the lagoon.<br>b) Deployment, repositioning, installation of HP fender backing boards, towing of HP fenders,<br>submarine camels, sea cushion fenders and maintenance of NAVAID and fleet mooring buoys.<br>c) Retrieval/Deployment of submarine towed array sonar system (STASS) cable.<br>d) Assistance to Navy Underwater Construction Team (NUCT) or other diver inspection teams<br>performing U/W inspection of buoys, piers and markers; and to divers conducting hull cleaning,<br>inspection and U/W jobs for COMPSRON TWO ships.<br>e) MWR activities and chartered fishing trips, lagoon water sampling and special runs for VIP<br>repatriations or MEDEVACs.<br>f) Installation/positioning/retrieval of oil booms for ships, fuel barges and small craft operations.<br>g) Operation of YOS Potable water barge, SWOB, YC-SLOPS and YC-CARGO barge.<br>h) Search and Rescue operation and waterborne oil spill response, mitigation and clean-up.<br>i) Emergency requirements and other boat service assistance required in the lagoon.<br>j) Fueling of craft in Small Boat Basin (SBB), removal of bilge oily water and cleaning of boat.<br>k) Dock and sea trials of LCMs, small boats and service crafts after repair/maintenance.<br>l) Mooring and unmooring of ships to/from Fleet Mooring Buoys and support to line handling of ships.<br>&bull; Performs assigned scheduled (PMS) maintenance requirements on boat and onboard equipment, iaw<br>Navy\'s 3-M System.<br>&bull; Participates in dock and sea trials of LCMs after repair/maintenance, ensuring boats are safe,<br>operational and seaworthy.<br>&bull; Participates in monthly oil spill drill and quarterly oil spill training, and NSF-DG Annual Facility<br>Response Training, accordingly.<br>&bull; Provides assistance to passengers in boarding and disembarking from craft and ensure that the boat<br>captain is informed/advised of any situation/incidents accordingly.<br>&bull; Provides medical first aid assistance and renders CPR to passengers experiencing health or physical<br>difficulties/injuries until the rescue or assistance arrives.<br>&bull; In the event the boat captain is physically incapacitated to perform his duties, incumbent operates the<br>radio communication system and maintains constant communication to Port Control Tower reporting<br>and receiving information/instructions, handles the boat safely and in seaworthy manner until the<br>rescue or assistance arrives.<br>&bull; Perform duties as look-out to assist LCM Captain in the safe operation of LCM/Utility Boats, Rapid<br>Response Skimmer (RRS) and other tasks required to support contract requirements of A-06.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Must speak, read and understand English language both orally and in writing.<br>&bull; Must complete the On-the-job Training (OJT) for LCM Deckhands, including oil spill training.<br>&bull; Must have knowledge in Boat Handling and Seamanship Skill, basic radio communications and use of<br>firefighting equipment.<br>&bull; Must have knowledge in Medical First Aid and Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR).<br>&bull; Must pass 2nd Class Swimmer qualification level<br>&bull; Must pass the overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Boat Handling and Seamanship Skill Training.<br>&bull; On-the-Job Training for LCM Deckhands.<br>&bull; First Aid/CPR certificate and 2nd Class Swimmer certificate.<br>&bull; Certified PQS 301 (Maintenance Personnel), Personnel Qualification Standard for Ship\'s Maintenance<br>and Material (3M) System.<br>&bull; NSF-DG Facility Response Training</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>EDUCATION</strong>:<br>&bull; 1)Diploma graduate or its equivalent.<br>&bull; 2) Attended formal education in maritime studies or equivalent training is preferred but not necessary.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE:</strong><br>Minimum of one (1) year experience aboard vessel as Deckhand.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 510', 2, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 13:18:48', '2025-05-26 14:03:58', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(40, 1, NULL, NULL, 'CIVIL/STRUCTURAL ENGINEER', 'civilstructural-engineer', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Performs all aspects of work necessary for development of all civil engineering aspects of in-house designs,<br>such as engineering and economic studies, project development, design analyses and computations,<br>drawings specifications, cost estimates, project schedules, technical consultation designs, and other aspects<br>of projects development and designs.<br>&bull; Knowledgeable on different structural systems such as column supports both steel and concrete, transformer<br>pads, wharfs, piers, pump house, steel truss member designs, roof sections to include purlins, concrete and<br>panel roofs, roads, building foundations, runway repairs including concrete/asphalt and drainage, shoreline<br>revetments, standalone structures, and various concrete buildings up to 3 stories high, and radome.<br>&bull; Prepares technical sections of the Government Request for Proposals (RFPs).<br>&bull; Serves as Project Design Engineer for the design of substantial new construction, renovation, and<br>improvement projects for real property facilities, encompassing highly specialized or unique requirements,<br>accomplished by in-house or by Architect-Engineer (A-E) forces.<br>&bull; Provides technical reviews of design calculations, analyses, drawings and specifications for A-E designs<br>and design/build contractor submittal to ensure compliance with project objectives and standards; and<br>prepares engineering reports, cost estimates, analyses, and justification data.<br>&bull; Provides timely and thorough technical consultation that recommends solutions to remediate deficiencies<br>effectively and efficiently.<br>&bull; Performs other duties as assigned.</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Knowledge in structural design involving reinforced concrete, steel, timber.<br>&bull; Knowledge in structural rehabilitations and renovations of buildings and structures.<br>&bull; Ability to do analysis of Civil/Structural engineering problems.<br>&bull; Ability to translate into engineering design or engineering study recommendations.<br>&bull; Must be familiar with the latest Civil/Structural codes and standards.<br>&bull; Will be required to calculate shore supporting, safety ratings for working platforms, loading of roof structures<br>on building verticals, machinery loading and force evaluations for stress, tension, and shear as well as<br>moment of inertia.<br>&bull; Measure soil loading and water percolation rates, confirm concrete test results, elevations for drainage, and<br>inspection of water tanks.<br>&bull; Be able to calculate safe work loading of elevated platforms and working at height support to include ladders<br>and lifts.<br>&bull; Must have good oral and written communication skills which enable effective liaison with clients, other<br>departments within the organization, subcontractors, and clients, reports directly to Senior Management.<br>&bull; Particular attention to details, good project management and leadership skills.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must be contract oriented and computer literate in Microsoft Office software.<br>&bull; Must possess passport book (not passport card) with at least 12 months of remaining validity and with at<br>least 6 blank visa/stamp pages remaining.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong><br>&bull; Must have Engineering license by the Government of nationality<br>▪ Registered Civil Engineer<br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must have a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Civil Engineering based on a four-year course of study from an accredited<br>university or college is required. With U.S. equivalence for a non-U.S. Citizen is highly desired.<br><strong>EXPERIENCE</strong>:<br>&bull; Must have at least five (5) years&rsquo; experience in Civil/Structural Engineering design.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 1,600', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 13:34:06', '2025-05-26 14:01:52', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(41, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Heavy Equipment Operator', 'heavy-equipment-operator', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION OF JOB TASK AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br>&bull; Operates and maintains a variety of heavy vehicles and other equipment.<br>&bull; Loads and unloads supplies and equipment from ships, docks, warehouses, and motor vehicles, and moves<br>hazardous materials as required.<br>&bull; Operates all types of Construction/Heavy Equipment for Base Support such as bulldozer, grader, bucket loader,<br>backhoe, sweeper, water distributor truck, ditching machine, auger truck, road roller, transit mixer truck, etc.<br>&bull; Equipment is used to excavate, load, or move dirt, gravel, or non-hazardous and hazardous materials.<br>&bull; Performs routine inspection and maintenance on vehicles such as checking oil, water, and tires.<br>&bull; Performs pre-service maintenance checks and indicates findings.<br>&bull; Records malfunctions of other items requiring attention as observed during the working day.<br>&bull; Records the number of gallons of fuel issued to the equipment while in his custody.<br>&bull; Completes records, maintains tools and equipment, and performs various clean-up and housekeeping activities.<br>&bull; Observes and follows all safety rules and procedures, including wearing required personal protective equipment.<br>&bull; Performs other duties and activities as directed.</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>BASIC JOB QUALIFICATIONS: (Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs)</strong><br>&bull; Ability to operate heavy equipment.<br>&bull; Considerable knowledge and skill in the operation and servicing of various automotive and complex<br>construction equipment.<br>&bull; Considerable knowledge of the hazards involved in equipment operation and the safety precautions necessary.<br>&bull; Knowledge of basic vehicle inspection and maintenance, including tire pressure, and checking oil and water<br>levels.<br>&bull; Must speak, read, and understand the English Language.<br>&bull; Must pass overseas medical screening and be in good health.<br>&bull; Must have a valid driver\'s license with the following license codes (2, 3, and 8 or B, B1, D, BE, and CE).</p>\r\n<p><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING</strong>:<br>&bull; Must be fully qualified and capable of being certified IAW NAVFAC P-300.<br>&bull; Completed any of the following Heavy Equipment Operation training and certification is highly desired:<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Backhoe Loader)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Bulldozer)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Transit Mixer Truck)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Forklift)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Motor Grader)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Wheel Loader)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (On-Highway Dump Truck - Rigid)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Hydraulic Excavator)<br>▪ Heavy Equipment Operation (Road Roller)\\</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br>&bull; Must have at least a diploma, a Technical or Vocational course Graduate is required.<br>EXPERIENCE:<br>&bull; Must have at least five (5) years of experience as Heavy Equipment Operator and in-plant operations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs and documents to <em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em><strong>a</strong> by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 600', 1, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-26 14:00:39', '2025-05-26 14:01:14', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1);
