-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">All work-related training certificates</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Passport Copy</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">COVID-19 vaccination certificate</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Employment certificate/ Recommendation letter</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>JOB SPECIFICATIONS: SPECIAL CERTIFICATIONS OR TRAINING:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Any Welding certification/s is highly desired.</li>\r\n<li>Flux-Cored Arc Welding (FCAW)</li>\r\n<li>Gas Metal Arc Welding (GMAW)</li>\r\n<li>Gas Tungsten Arc Welding (GTAW)</li>\r\n<li>Shielded Arc Welding (SMAW)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>EDUCATION:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A diploma, Technical, or Vocational course graduate is required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>EXPERIENCE</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Must have at least five (5) years of experience in welding as a Foreman, Leadman, or Supervisory capacity<br>of various construction projects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">NB/;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Qualified and interested applicants who meet the specifications are requested to send their updated CVs to&nbsp;<em><strong>vacancies@amsol.afric</strong></em>a by 25th June 2025.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>*Kindly indicate the position applied for in the subject line of the email</li>\r\n<li>Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, '$ 510', 3, 'full-time', 'Diego Garcia, UK', 106, NULL, '2025-05-29 09:32:50', '2025-05-29 09:35:59', 'open', '2025-06-25', 1),
(45, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Pharmacist', 'pharmacist', '<p><strong>Role Summary</strong><br>Responsible for monitoring the supply of all medicines used in the hospital and are in charge of<br>purchasing, manufacturing, dispensing, and quality testing their medication stock along with help<br>from pharmacy assistants and pharmacy technicians.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Make sure medicines are stored appropriately and securely.</li>\r\n<li>Follow guidelines for drug use within the hospital and implement<br>hospital regulations</li>\r\n<li>Order and purchase pharmaceutical supplies, medical supplies, or<br>drugs, maintaining stock and storing and handling it properly</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and quality-check sterile medications, for example,<br>intravenous medications</li>\r\n<li>Set up and supervise clinical trials</li>\r\n<li>Document errors and communicate them to the nursing and<br>pharmacy staff</li>\r\n<li>Verify expiry dates of drugs prior to dispensing medication to<br>patients/customers.</li>\r\n<li>Receive, return and update drug credits on the system in a timely<br>manner.</li>\r\n<li>Comply and observe the environmental health and safety measures<br>and regulations by proper handling, storage and dispensing of<br>medications</li>\r\n<li>Record, monitor and update the expiry list of medications in timely<br>manner</li>\r\n<li>Conduct Floor inspections once a month for all ward stock,<br>solutions and patient medication left behind</li>\r\n<li>Perform random medication checks daily and monitor variance<br>levels in your respective satellites.</li>\r\n<li>Reporting of any breakages and any observance that needs attention<br>by management.</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance of client&rsquo;s and institution&rsquo;s data records as private and<br>confidential.</li>\r\n<li>Be keen and pay attention to the doctors&rsquo; needs and preferences to<br>medications to ensure the pharmacy is well stocked at all times.</li>\r\n<li>Strictly monitor the use of DDA drugs &amp; limit their use to<br>prescription only. Maintain a strict stock control on DDA<br>medication &amp; verify stock of DDA medications on a daily basis,<br>reporting any mishaps to the relevant authorities.<br>Perform any other duties as may be assigned as per hospital<br>demands, from time to time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">A Bachelor\'s degree in Pharmacy from a recognized university</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Registered with the Pharmaceutical and Poisons Board of Kenya.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Valid Practicing License from the Pharmacy and Poisons Board.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Minimum of 2 years of hospital or clinical pharmacy preferred</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Strong attention to detail and excellent communication</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Competitive', 1, 'full-time', 'Nairobi, Kenya', 106, NULL, '2025-05-30 12:41:03', '2025-07-08 14:03:40', 'open', '2025-07-16', 1),
(46, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Tender Intern', 'tender-intern', '<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Duration: </strong>3 months</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">We are seeking a detail-oriented Tender Intern to join our team. This internship offers a valuable opportunity to gain hands-on experience in the tendering and bidding process, supporting our efforts to secure new projects and contracts. The intern will assist in various stages of the process.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">&middot; Diligently search for and evaluate tenders from a wide range of sources.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">&middot; Support the tender team in reviewing tender documents, including RFPs, RFQs, and ITTs, to understand requirements and deadlines.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">&middot; Assist with compiling and organizing necessary documentation for tender submissions, ensuring accuracy, completeness, and compliance with all specifications.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">&middot; Assist with administrative tasks related to the tendering process, including photocopying, scanning, and binding.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Diploma or recently completed Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration, Procurement, Project Management, or a related field.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Basic understanding of tendering processes is a plus but not required.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What We Offer:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Valuable hands-on experience in the tendering and business development field.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Exposure to diverse projects and industries.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; A supportive and collaborative work environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>To Apply:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Interested candidates should submit their CV outlining their interest in the tender internship to<strong> <a href=\"www.amsol.africa/jobs\">www.amsol.africa/jobs</a></strong></p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 'contract', 'Nairobi', 150, NULL, '2025-06-18 14:20:27', '2025-06-18 14:29:27', 'open', '2025-06-27', 1),
(47, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Primary School Teacher (British Curriculum, Grades 1-6) MATH, GEOGRAPHY, SCIENCE', 'primary-school-teacher-british-curriculum-grades-1-6-math-geography-science', '<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p>\r\n<p>Our client is seeking an enthusiastic and experienced Primary School Teacher to join their dedicated team. The successful candidate will be responsible for delivering the British Curriculum to students between Grades 1-6. Your role will create a dynamic and engaging learning environment that promotes academic excellence and the holistic development of each child. This role requires a passionate educator who is knowledgeable about the British Curriculum, child-centered learning, and committed to fostering a love of learning in primary-aged students.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Curriculum Planning and Delivery: Plan, prepare, and deliver engaging and differentiated lessons in line with the British Curriculum framework for Grades 1-6 across a range of subjects (including but not limited to English, Mathematics, Science, Humanities, and the Arts).</p>\r\n<p>&middot; British Curriculum Expertise: Demonstrate a strong understanding of the British Curriculum framework and its assessment methods for primary education.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Effective Teaching Methodologies: Utilize a variety of effective teaching strategies to cater to diverse learning styles and abilities, including inquiry-based learning, collaborative projects, and the integration of technology.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Assessment and Progress Monitoring: Implement formative and summative assessment strategies to monitor student progress, provide constructive feedback, and inform future teaching. Maintain accurate records of student attainment and development.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Classroom Management and Environment: Create and maintain a positive, well-managed, and stimulating classroom environment that is conducive to effective learning, collaboration, and student well-being.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Differentiation and Inclusion: Differentiate instruction to meet the individual learning needs of all students, including those with special educational needs and English as an Additional Language (EAL) learners.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Communication and Collaboration: Establish and maintain effective communication with parents, colleagues, and school leadership regarding student progress, classroom activities, and school events. Collaborate effectively with other teachers and support staff to ensure a cohesive and supportive learning environment.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Pastoral Care: Provide support and guidance to students, addressing their social, emotional, and personal development outside of academics and fostering a sense of community within the school.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Professional Development: Actively engage in professional development opportunities to stay current with best practices in primary education and the British Curriculum.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Safeguarding and Child Protection: Uphold the school\'s commitment to safeguarding and child protection, ensuring the safety and well-being of all students at all times.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Bachelor\'s Degree in Education</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Proven experience teaching the British Curriculum at the primary level (Grades 1-6) is essential.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Experience teaching in a multicultural and international school setting is desirable.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Excellent communication, interpersonal, and classroom management skills.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Strong organizational and planning skills.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Proficiency in using technology to enhance teaching and learning.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; A passion for primary education and a commitment to student success.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Desired Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Child-centered and nurturing approach to teaching.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Creative and innovative teaching style.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Commitment to inclusive education and meeting diverse learning needs.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Strong team player with excellent collaborative skills.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Adaptability, flexibility, and resilience.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Excellent command of written and spoken English.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Incentives</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Competitive Compensation</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Career Growth</p>\r\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>\r\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to submit the following documents via our online portal; <a href=\"www.amsol.africa\">www.amsol.africa</a></p>\r\n<p>&middot; A cover letter outlining your suitability for the position, your educational philosophy, and experience with the British Curriculum.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; A detailed resume/curriculum vitae (CV).</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Contact details for at least three professional referees.</p>', NULL, NULL, 2, 'full-time', 'Nairobi', 150, NULL, '2025-06-18 14:27:27', '2025-06-19 06:58:30', 'open', '2025-06-27', 1),
(48, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Medical Sales and Marketing Representative', 'medical-sales-and-marketing-representative', '<p><strong>Reports To: Sales Manager / Business Development Manager</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Job Summary: </strong>We are seeking a highly motivated and results-driven Medical Sales and Marketing Representative to join our dynamic team. The successful candidate will be responsible for promoting and selling a diverse range of medical products to healthcare institutions and professionals within an assigned territory in Kenya. This role requires a strong understanding of the medical sector.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Identify and prospect new sales opportunities within hospitals, clinics, laboratories, pharmacies, government health facilities, and other healthcare providers.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Develop and implement strategic sales plans to expand market share and client base.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Provide valuable market insights by staying ahead of market trends</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Develop in-depth knowledge of all products in the company\'s portfolio, including technical specifications, clinical applications, and competitive advantages.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Prepare sales proposals, quotations and contracts efficiently.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Conduct compelling product presentations and demonstrations to healthcare professionals, showcasing the features, benefits, and value proposition of our medical supplies.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Prepare and submit accurate sales forecasts, activity reports, and customer feedback.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications &amp; Experience:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Degree or Diploma in Medical Sciences, Pharmacy, Nursing, Biomedical Engineering, Business Administration, Marketing, or a related field.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Minimum of 2-3 years of proven sales experience in the medical or pharmaceutical fields.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Strong understanding of the Kenyan healthcare system, procurement processes, and relevant regulations.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What We Offer:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot; Competitive salary and attractive commission structure.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Opportunities for professional growth and career advancement.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; A supportive and collaborative work environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>\r\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to submit the following documents via our online portal; <a href=\"www.amsol.africa\">www.amsol.africa</a></p>\r\n<p>&middot; A cover letter outlining your suitability for the position.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; A detailed resume/curriculum vitae (CV) including your qualifications and experience.</p>\r\n<p>&middot; Contact details for at least three referees.</p>', NULL, NULL, 10, 'full-time', 'Nairobi, Kenya (with travel across assigned region)', 150, NULL, '2025-06-18 14:33:19', '2025-06-19 06:58:03', 'open', '2025-07-18', 1),
(49, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Lead – Regional Finance', 'lead-regional-finance', '<p><strong>Purpose of the role</strong><br>- To carry out day to day financial Operational activities within the given region<br>- To ensure accurate maintenance of accounts, book keeping, MIS Reporting, Statutory<br>Compliance &amp; Branch Control.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Areas of Responsibility &amp; brief description</strong><br><strong>Responsibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Preparation of MIS/Ledger independently and ensure correct and<br>complete accounting including all necessary reports to<br>HO<br>2. Checking bank statement for cash &amp; DD credit and maintain the same in<br>remittance tracker and Making DAR Reports and reconciling with the<br>Online Fund Flow.<br>3. Preparation of Month end provision and Intercompany Reconciliation.<br>4. Ensure maintenance of Internal customer satisfaction index for the<br>department<br>5. Accurate &amp; timely Verification of travel sheet and Imprest clearance.<br>6. Ensure verification of vendor invoices &amp; payment documents.<br>7. Ensure timely remittance &amp; RTGS &amp; maintain complete documentation.<br>8. Coordination with SSC and VFS Global staff for payment and other<br>Queries.<br>9. Routine task like Stop payment, DD cancellation, cheque cancellation,<br>cheque deposition, receipt and manual payment.<br>10. Coordination with the Travel desk for surrendered currency and correct<br>accounting in SAP.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Qualification &amp; Experience</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Education:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Graduate in Commerce &amp; Accounts or Any other Equivalent Degree<br>Additional: Post Graduate/ MBA in Finance<br>Experience: Ideally 2 &ndash; 3 years&rsquo; experience in Finance &amp; Accounts<br>Knowledge &amp; Key Skills: Proficiency with Microsoft Office</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '100000', 1, 'full-time', 'Nairobi, Kenya', 106, NULL, '2025-06-19 13:10:55', '2025-06-19 13:12:00', 'open', '2025-06-27', 1),
(50, 1, NULL, NULL, 'HR Consultant', 'hr-consultant', '<h3 data-start=\"395\" data-end=\"413\"><strong data-start=\"399\" data-end=\"411\">About Us</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"414\" data-end=\"805\">We are a dynamic HR consultancy firm dedicated to helping organizations unlock their full potential through customized people solutions. Our services include talent acquisition, HR audits, salary benchmarking, organizational development, and training programs. As we continue to grow, we are seeking an experienced <strong data-start=\"729\" data-end=\"755\">HR Consultancy Partner</strong> to join our team and lead key client engagements.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"807\" data-end=\"810\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"812\" data-end=\"835\"><strong data-start=\"816\" data-end=\"833\">Role Overview</strong></h3>\r\n<p data-start=\"836\" data-end=\"1230\">As an HR Consultancy Partner, you will serve as a strategic advisor to our clients, leading consultancy projects that focus on <strong data-start=\"963\" data-end=\"981\">salary surveys</strong>, <strong data-start=\"983\" data-end=\"1012\">compensation benchmarking</strong>, and <strong data-start=\"1018\" data-end=\"1063\">training program development and delivery</strong>. This is a client-facing leadership role ideal for a seasoned HR professional with strong consultancy experience and a passion for people and business transformation.</p>\r\n<hr data-start=\"1232\" data-end=\"1235\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"1237\" data-end=\"1265\"><strong data-start=\"1241\" data-end=\"1265\">Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1267\" data-end=\"2177\">\r\n<li data-start=\"1267\" data-end=\"1386\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1269\" data-end=\"1386\">Lead and manage end-to-end <strong data-start=\"1296\" data-end=\"1331\">salary and compensation surveys</strong>, including benchmarking, data analysis, and reporting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1387\" data-end=\"1550\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1389\" data-end=\"1550\">Design and deliver <strong data-start=\"1408\" data-end=\"1445\">training and development programs</strong> tailored to client needs, from leadership development to employee engagement and performance management.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1551\" data-end=\"1658\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1553\" data-end=\"1658\">Develop and maintain strong client relationships, acting as a trusted HR advisor across multiple sectors.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1659\" data-end=\"1764\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1661\" data-end=\"1764\">Lead HR consultancy projects including HR audits, policy development, and organizational restructuring.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1765\" data-end=\"1863\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1767\" data-end=\"1863\">Conduct job evaluations and build pay structures in line with market trends and internal equity.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1864\" data-end=\"1943\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1866\" data-end=\"1943\">Oversee project teams to ensure quality, timeliness, and client satisfaction.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1944\" data-end=\"2076\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1946\" data-end=\"2076\">Contribute to business development efforts, including proposal writing, client presentations, and participation in pitch meetings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2077\" data-end=\"2177\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2079\" data-end=\"2177\">Stay abreast of labor market trends, HR best practices, and legal changes affecting HR operations.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr data-start=\"2179\" data-end=\"2182\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"2184\" data-end=\"2221\"><strong data-start=\"2188\" data-end=\"2221\">Qualifications and Experience</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2223\" data-end=\"2895\">\r\n<li data-start=\"2223\" data-end=\"2344\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2225\" data-end=\"2344\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Human Resources or related field.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2345\" data-end=\"2460\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2347\" data-end=\"2460\">A minimum of <strong data-start=\"2360\" data-end=\"2404\">10 years of progressive experience in HR</strong>, with at least 5 years in a <strong data-start=\"2433\" data-end=\"2459\">consulting environment</strong>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2461\" data-end=\"2580\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2463\" data-end=\"2580\">Proven expertise in <strong data-start=\"2483\" data-end=\"2501\">salary surveys</strong>, compensation and benefits, and <strong data-start=\"2534\" data-end=\"2579\">training program development and delivery</strong>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2581\" data-end=\"2680\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2583\" data-end=\"2680\">Strong understanding of labor laws, HR best practices, and organizational development strategies.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2681\" data-end=\"2750\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2683\" data-end=\"2750\">Excellent presentation, facilitation, and client management skills.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2751\" data-end=\"2827\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2753\" data-end=\"2827\">Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects and teams simultaneously.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2828\" data-end=\"2895\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2830\" data-end=\"2895\">Professional HR certification (e.g., SHRM, CIPD, CHRP) is a plus.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr data-start=\"2897\" data-end=\"2900\">\r\n<h3 data-start=\"2902\" data-end=\"2923\"><strong data-start=\"2906\" data-end=\"2923\">What We Offer</strong></h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2925\" data-end=\"3152\">\r\n<li data-start=\"2925\" data-end=\"2986\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2927\" data-end=\"2986\">Opportunity to work with diverse clients across industries.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2987\" data-end=\"3041\">\r\n<p data-start=\"2989\" data-end=\"3041\">Autonomy to lead projects and innovate HR solutions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"3042\" data-end=\"3102\">\r\n<p data-start=\"3044\" data-end=\"3102\">Competitive compensation and performance-based incentives.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"3103\" data-end=\"3152\">\r\n<p data-start=\"3105\" data-end=\"3152\">A collaborative, high-performance team culture.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'Competitive', 2, 'full-time', 'Nairobi, Kenya', 106, NULL, '2025-06-23 13:32:55', '2025-06-23 13:34:20', 'open', '2025-07-04', 1),
(51, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Deputy Manager – Administration', 'deputy-manager-administration', '<p><strong>Purpose of the role</strong><br>- To effectively manage general administration activities and proactively maintain<br>records of day-to-day activities - To undertake the responsibility of sourcing, procuring, maintenance &amp; invoicing<br>processing of office supplies &amp; other facilities, and amenities.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"541\" data-end=\"566\"><strong data-start=\"541\" data-end=\"566\">Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ol data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"1597\">\r\n<li data-start=\"567\" data-end=\"689\">\r\n<p data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"689\">Maintain records and ensure timely payment of bills for telephone, mobile, electricity, ACs, and other vendor services.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"690\" data-end=\"742\">\r\n<p data-start=\"693\" data-end=\"742\">Process material management payments through SAP.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"743\" data-end=\"820\">\r\n<p data-start=\"746\" data-end=\"820\">Ensure compliance with VFAR and purchase policy while processing invoices.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"821\" data-end=\"897\">\r\n<p data-start=\"824\" data-end=\"897\">Handle petty cash operations including vouchers and reports for payments.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"898\" data-end=\"970\">\r\n<p data-start=\"901\" data-end=\"970\">Coordinate procurement, repair, and maintenance of office facilities.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"971\" data-end=\"1064\">\r\n<p data-start=\"974\" data-end=\"1064\">Maintain accurate bookkeeping of MIS reports, audit documents, and contractual agreements.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1065\" data-end=\"1140\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1068\" data-end=\"1140\">Ensure compliance with ISO 14001 standards for environmental management.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1141\" data-end=\"1212\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1144\" data-end=\"1212\">Implement VFS Global\'s information security policies and procedures.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1213\" data-end=\"1283\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1216\" data-end=\"1283\">Manage shop licenses, certifications, and vendor contract renewals.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1284\" data-end=\"1367\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1288\" data-end=\"1367\">Respond to inquiries, troubleshoot issues, and ensure stakeholder satisfaction.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1368\" data-end=\"1442\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1372\" data-end=\"1442\">Oversee timely renewal of maintenance contracts and premises handover.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1443\" data-end=\"1521\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1447\" data-end=\"1521\">Assist in the sale of company assets and supervise refurbishment projects.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1522\" data-end=\"1597\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1526\" data-end=\"1597\">Promote judicious use of natural resources and adhere to EH&amp;S policies.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<hr data-start=\"1599\" data-end=\"1602\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1604\" data-end=\"1643\"><strong data-start=\"1604\" data-end=\"1643\">Indicative Key Result Areas (KRAs):</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-start=\"1644\" data-end=\"1868\">\r\n<li data-start=\"1644\" data-end=\"1673\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1646\" data-end=\"1673\">Cost-effective procurement.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1674\" data-end=\"1718\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1676\" data-end=\"1718\">Audit documentation and policy compliance.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1719\" data-end=\"1755\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1721\" data-end=\"1755\">Implementation of new initiatives.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1756\" data-end=\"1786\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1758\" data-end=\"1786\">Effective vendor management.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1787\" data-end=\"1828\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1789\" data-end=\"1828\">Internal customer satisfaction metrics.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"1829\" data-end=\"1868\">\r\n<p data-start=\"1831\" data-end=\"1868\">Timely processing of vendor invoices.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Qualifications &amp; Experience</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration or any other related field (Postgraduate qualification is an added advantage)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">2&ndash;6 years of relevant experience in administration or facility management</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Strong organizational and multitasking skills</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Knowledge of procurement, vendor coordination, and facility upkeep</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Ability to identify and implement process improvements</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">High level of professionalism, integrity, and attention to detail</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none\">Familiarity with SAP and ISO standards is a plus</span></li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'UGX 2,621,800.00.', 1, 'full-time', 'Kampala, Uganda', 106, NULL, '2025-06-26 13:20:44', '2025-07-04 05:28:06', 'open', '2025-07-18', 1);
