(53, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Theatre Nurse', 'theatre-nurse', '<p>Job Purpose<br>The theatre nurse shall be responsible in promoting and maintaining high standards of<br>professional nursing care by providing quality services with special focus on surgeries to meet<br>the needs of patients.</p>\r\n<p>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES.<br>SYSTEM</p>\r\n<p>● Managing human resources, equipment, and supplies for individualized<br>patient care<br>● Managing patient flow in theatre Department<br>● Participating in surgical procedures as a scrub nurse<br>● Institute measures to promote normal body temperature of the patient<br>during operation e.g., providing warm intravenous fluids<br>● Managing of consumable non&ndash;consumable surgical supplies<br>● Timely reporting of any malfunctioning equipment for repair<br>● Ensuring all patients are charged in relation to the procedure performed and<br>consumable supplies used e.g., drugs<br>● Monitoring of blood/fluid loss during operation<br>● Perform any other task delegated to by your seniors/team leader/manager</p>\r\n<p>PROCESS</p>\r\n<p>● Assessing patient\'s status, reviewing charts/file, identifying patient and<br>verifying surgical site upon arrival from the ward<br>● Take measures to ensure patient\'s comfort and provision of psychological<br>support to the patient<br>● Participate in packaging, Sterilization and dispatching of theatre<br>consumables<br>● Maintaining aseptic /safe controlled environment<br>● Receiving patients from ward, confirming theatre list, and handing over<br>patients once stable enough to be in the ward<br>● Transferring patient to operating room table, Participate in Positioning the<br>patient on the operating table and to recovery area after operation<br>● Ensures that the sponge, needle, and instrument counts are correct before<br>and after the procedure<br>● Determine patient\'s immediate response to surgical intervention by doing<br>assessment<br>● Maintain patient\'s safety (airway, circulation, and prevention of injury)<br>● Administer medications, fluid and blood if Prescribed<br>● Report patient\'s response to surgical procedure and anesthesia<br>● Describe intra-operative factors e.g., insertion of drains, administration of<br>blood, analgesic agents, or other medications during surgery and<br>occurrence of unexpected events<br>● Taking vital observations before/after surgery and reporting any changes in<br>patient\'s vital signs<br>● Ensuring theatre equipment are in good working condition<br>● Documenting any events during surgery<br>● Follow the orientation guidelines issued with the timelines allocated<br>● Any other duties that may be allocated by the Management/Supervisor</p>\r\n<p><strong>PEOPLE INTERNAL</strong><br>Managing and Communicating patient\'s emotional status to other appropriate<br>theatre team members<br>Communicating intra-operative information to the respective ward staff including<br>type of surgery performed and anesthetic used<br>EXTERNAL<br>Communicating to relevant parties e.g., Anesthetists, Surgeons and MO\'s<br>Assisting anesthetists during induction</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong><br>● Diploma in Community health Nursing (KRCHN) or BScN<br>from a recognized institution.<br>● Higher Diploma in Perioperative Nursing will be an added<br>advantage<br>● Valid Nursing license<br>● Registered by the Nursing Council</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>Experience </strong></p>\r\n<p>● At least Three years of experience in Perioperative Nursing<br>Required license/<br>certificate<br>● Certificate of Good Conduct<br>● Must have Certification in BLS<br>● ACLS Certification will be an added advantage<br>● Experience in Laparoscopy will be an added advantage</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>Essential skills and</strong><br><strong>competencies</strong><br>● Excellent clinical acumen.<br>● Excellent customer service skills.<br>● Effective communication skills - listening, oral and written.<br>● Good interpersonal skills and a team player.<br>● Empathetic to patients of all ages.<br>● Ability to work under pressure with minimum supervision.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>Job Conditions </strong></p>\r\n<p>● May be exposed to biohazards during regular hospital duties<br>● Environment may be physically and emotionally<br>demanding, working under stressful conditions<br>● Work is carried out in shifts that ensure coverage</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'Competitive', 1, 'full-time', 'Nairobi, Kenya', 106, NULL, '2025-07-08 14:02:48', '2025-07-17 09:04:18', 'open', '2025-07-31', 1);
